#. type: Title ==
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/system-groups.adoc:68
#, no-wrap
msgid "Work with Groups"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/system-groups.adoc:72
msgid ""
"When you have your clients arranged into groups, you can use your groups to "
"manage updates.  For Salt clients, you can also apply states and formulas to "
"all clients in a group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/system-groups.adoc:76
msgid ""
"In the {productname} {webui}, navigate to menu:Systems[System Groups].  The "
"list shows an icon if there are updates available for any of the clients in "
"the group.  Click the icon to see more information about the updates "
"available and to apply them to the clients."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/system-groups.adoc:79
msgid ""
"You can also work with more than one group at a time.  Select the groups you "
"want to work with, and click btn:[Work with union] to select every client in "
"every selected group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/client-configuration/pages/system-groups.adoc:83
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can work on intersections of groups.  Select two or more "
"groups, and click btn:[Work with intersection] to select only those clients "
"that exist in all the selected groups.  For example, you might have one "
"group for all Salt clients, and another group for all SLES clients.  The "
"intersection of these groups would be all Salt SLES clients."
msgstr ""
